\par \cf4   ## What not to rely on Sloyd for first\cf1 
\par 
\par \cf4   I would avoid making these your first AI-generated targets:\cf1 
\par 
\par \cf4   * final hero characters\cf1 
\par \cf4   * animation-ready infantry bodies\cf1 
\par \cf4   * horses with production-ready rigs\cf1 
\par \cf4   * facially expressive nobles\cf1 
\par \cf4   * complicated siege engines with many moving parts\cf1 
\par 
\par \cf4\f1   Sloyd\rquote s strengths are its text/image generation and procedural, game-oriented asset creation, but AI 3D generally still needs cleanup and is strongest on props/background assets. ([Sloyd][1])\cf1\f0 
\par 
\par \cf4   ## Recommended production order\cf1 
\par 
\par \cf4   Build in this order:\cf1 
\par 
\par \cf4   **Phase 1**\cf1 
\par 
\par \cf4   * barrels, crates, sacks, carts, fences, tents, banners, market stalls, palisades\cf1 
\par 
\par \cf4   **Phase 2**\cf1 
\par 
\par \cf4   * village houses, chapels, workshops, bridges, watchtowers\cf1 
\par 
\par \cf4   **Phase 3**\cf1 
\par 
\par \cf4   * castle modules, throne room props, faction heraldry sets\cf1 
\par 
\par \cf4   **Phase 4**\cf1 
\par 
\par \cf4   * weapon racks, armor props, destruction variants, special landmarks\cf1 
\par 
\par \cf4   That order gets you to a playable vertical slice fastest.\cf1 
\par 
\par \cf4   ## Best prompting strategy\cf1 
\par 
\par \cf4   For Sloyd text prompts, keep them structured:\cf1 
\par 
\par \cf4   * object\cf1 
\par \cf4   * era/style\cf1 
\par \cf4   * material\cf1 
\par \cf4   * silhouette\cf1 
\par \cf4   * detail level\cf1 
\par \cf4   * game style\cf1 
\par 
\par \cf4   Example:\cf1 
\par 
\par \cf4\f1   * \ldblquote low-poly medieval grain cart, rough oak wood, iron-rimmed wheels, game-ready, slightly stylized, worn but usable\rdblquote\cf1\f0 
\par \cf4\f1   * \ldblquote feudal banner stand, red and black heraldry, carved oak pole, brass finial, readable from distance, strategy game prop\rdblquote\cf1\f0 
\par 
\par \cf4   Use image-first only for:\cf1 
\par 
\par \cf4   * a specific crown design\cf1 
\par \cf4   * a unique imperial throne\cf1 
\par \cf4   * a faction-defining helmet\cf1 
\par \cf4   * a sacred relic\cf1 
\par \cf4   * a recognizable silhouette you want repeated consistently\cf1 
\par 
\par \cf4   ## Final recommendation\cf1 
\par 
\par \cf4   For this project:\cf1 
\par 
\par \cf4   **Default:** Sloyd text-to-3D\cf1 
\par \cf4   **Use image-first:** only for hero props and faction-defining pieces\cf1 
\par \cf4\f1   **Do not do DALL\'b7E-first for everything**\cf1\f0 
\par 
\par \cf4\f1   That will be faster, cheaper, and more consistent with Sloyd\rquote s strengths as a game-asset tool. ([Sloyd][1])\cf1\f0 
